<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-041-033 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 335 225</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  Oct 1 1991 v5 n33 p9(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Coastal Associates Publishing L.P. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Hand-held Psion PC weighs 9 ounces, offers Mac links. (PsionInc.'s Series 3 hand-held computer)(brief article) (productannouncement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Cohen, Raines.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Psion Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Psion Series 3 (Portable computer) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Hand-held computersProduct IntroductionBundled Software.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Raines CohenandM;Watertown, Conn.andP;  -- Psion Inc. last week shipped the Series 3, a pocket-sizePC-compatible with Mac transfer software.andP;  The tiny hand-held unit comes withseveral applications and has more storage than most other units of its size.andM;The Series 3 measures just 6.5 by 3.3 by 0.9 inches, and weighs a mere 9ounces.andP;  It opens up like a clamshell to reveal a 240-by-80-pixel screen anda QWERTY keyboard.andP;  Two AA batteries power it for two to four months.andM;Although no mouse or pointing device is used with the Series 3, the softwareincluded features a consistent, keyboard-driven graphical user interface.andO;The unit comes with a Microsoft Word-compatible word processor, as well as amultifile database, touch-tone dialer, agenda manager (with alarms) andcalculator.andP;  A Lotus 1-2-3-compatible spreadsheet will be sold next year.andM;The Series 3 comes with 384 Kbytes of ROM.andP;  It offers 128 Kbytes or 256Kbytes of RAM in its $425 and $495 configurations, respectively.andP;  Inaddition, two solid-state disk drives can accommodate non-volatilesolid-state disks, matchbook-size removable cartridges containingbattery-backed RAM or Flash EPROM, as well as ROM-based software.andP;  Thecompany sells the cartridges, containing up to 2 Mbytes of EPROM, for $150 to$600.andM;The system includes a serial port, but using it requires a $99 custom cableand Mac (or DOS) file transfer software.andM;Users may eventually be able to transfer information from the Series 3without any cables.andP;  RAM Mobile Data of New York and Ericsson GE Mobile DataInc. of Paramus, N.J., announced plans to integrate the Series 3 into the RAMMobile Data Network.andP;  With the network, Series 3 users will be able toconnect to electronic mail and other computer systems from the field via aportable radio modem.andM;Psion Inc. is at 118 Echo Lake Road, Watertown, Conn.andP;  06795.andP;  Phone (203)274-7521 or (800) 628-7949; fax (203) 274-7976.andO;</TEXT></DOC>